@NODE CD-ROM "CD-ROM Support!"

What this involves is a simple method of updating the number of downloads on
a given file.

The file has to be a normally uploaded file, with associated .fd file.

A special file is created in the users private directory which holds the list
of CD-ROM files tagged. The included batch file is used to do batch
downloads. After the download is completed, the 2 lists are compared, and
appropriate changes made.

For this to be fully effective, you MUST use the entire M-Tag suite. This
includes the batch list editors, and the separate tagging utility which
replaces the standard single file tag.

If you wish to use other tagging or batch editing programs, the .CDL file
won't be created (unless that program handles it). If you don't have a CD-ROM
then the .CDL file is not important, and should never be created unless your
files have incorrect filenotes.

The unregistered version will function enough to enable correct handling of
the special .CDL file. The M-Support program is not restricted.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Require "Requirements for M-Tag package"

The programs included in the M-Tag package should run on any Amiga with
@{b}OS2.0@{bu} or greater.

Several programs are required to use the View archive option available in
M-TagFS:

     LhA   - Used for .LHA, .LZH, and .RUN self extracting archives.
     Zoo   - Used for .ZOO files
     UnZip - Used for .ZIP files. Probably best use UnZip 5.2
     UnArj - Used for .ARJ files.
     DMS   - Used to view .DMS files.
     ARC   - Used for .ARC files.

These are the programs which are listed in the default config file.

The program 'DLGUpload' by Michael Dreher is also required when using the
pack option.

dlg.library is also required.

M-TagFS will require a base 240K regardless of how many files are in the area.
Should the number of files exceed a certain limit, you will get an 'Out of
memory error' produced in '@{"LOGS:M-Error.log" Link Error}'. I have a test area with 645
files and it was handled with no problems.

More RAM will be required to view archives/text files etc. but no more than
any other program.

Serious error output is logged to '@{"LOGS:M-Error.log" Link Error}'.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Error " Error output"

When any of the M-Tag package programs abort due to an error, the error is
logged in the file 'LOGS:M-Error.log'.

When making bug reports, always check this file first.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Registered_version "Registered version"

When you register the M-Tag package you will receive a keyfile. This keyfile
will unlock all the features of the programs.

Your keyfile will come direct from me via crashmail to your BBS.

@ENDNODE

