@NODE Program_Support " Supporting the .CDL file"

Programmers who write file utilities which add/remove files from the batch
list can also change the .CDL file.

Programmers may also make use of the .MArea file. Programmers should not
add/remove to this list unless they are doing a FULL security check on the
area. This means reading in the 'user.file' file for each area and checking
for correct security.

The included M-Tag.h should be satisfactory for c programmers (I don't
program in c!).

@ENDNODE

@NODE Future " Whats to come?

The M-Tag package is reaching its limits of expandability. The one major
addition will be CD-ROM support. This will allow the sysop to upload a CD-ROM
to his system in the normal fashion, and then delete all the #?.fd files.

This function is taking more time than I had expected. If only MagicFile was
still being worked on :-)

Feature's which are suggested will be added if possible.

@ENDNODE

@node keyfile "Invalid keyfile"

Some sysops may have been lucky enough to download the release of the M-Tag
package released onto AmiNet which had my keyfile in the archive.

If you are such a sysop, be warned that all updates AND any new utilities I
release will NOT function if this invalid keyfile is detected.

@ENDNODE

